parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission gears can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's transmission gears shatter or chip
causing metal debris to float in the casing
which can lead to additional damage to other parts and potentially cause the vehicle to lock up or malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pickup tube can cause the engine to seize, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The oil pickup tube breaks
causing the oil in the oil pan to not circulate through the system
which can destroy internal bearings and fatigue other engine internals.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leak and Raw Fuel Smell during Cold Starts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel leak and raw fuel smell during cold starts can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to accidents or injuries, and may also lead to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: Strong smell of gasoline inside and outside the vehicle during and after cold starts
visual evidence of fuel leakage under the intake manifold
fuel puddles on top of the engine block
and the smell of gasoline persists for an extended period.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Secondary Air Injection System Switching Valve Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the secondary air injection system switching valve can cause the valve to stick open, leading to emissions system problems, decreased engine performance, and potentially causing damage to the engine and catalytic converter.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
the vehicle may experience decreased engine performance
and the emissions system may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pick-up line can cause the oil light to flicker or stay on, leading to engine damage, including a cracked line and potentially requiring a replaced long block and turbo.
symptoms: The oil light flickers on and then stays on at idle or under low revs
indicating low oil pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the secondary air injection pump can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to vehicle damage or injury.
symptoms: The secondary air injection pump fails to turn off
causing a potential fire hazard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pickup tube can cause oil starvation, leading to catastrophic engine damage, requiring expensive repairs or replacement of the engine.
symptoms: The engine oil pressure light comes on
indicating low oil pressure
and upon inspection
aluminum shavings are found in the oil
and the oil pickup tube is broken.
